Watch Mode
	tsc first.ts -w
	tsc first.ts -watch
	  Keep recompiling first.ts, whenever any change happens in first.ts
	
  
Compiling the entire project/Multiple files
	tsc --init    //created tsconfig.json
	tsc   //All .ts file compile 
	tsc -watch    //All .ts file compile autometically whenever makes change
	

Including & Excluding files
	In tsconfig.json
		"exclude":["first.ts","second.ts"]
		"exclude":["*.dev.ts"]
		"exclude":["**/*.dev.ts"]
		"exclude":["node_modules"]
		
		"include":["first.ts","second.ts"]
		"include":["*.dev.ts"]
		"include":["**/*.dev.ts"]
		"include":["node_modules"]
		
		"files":["first.ts", "second.ts"] //Here we cannot include path
		
Setting a compilation target
 	In tsconfig.json - 
	    /* Specify ECMAScript target version: 'ES3' (default), 'ES5', 'ES2015', 'ES2016', 'ES2017','ES2018' or 'ESNEXT'. */
	    "target": "es5",                          
		
